<div class="help-content-wrap"><h3 id="was-your-deposit-unsuccessful-">Was your deposit unsuccessful?</h3>
<p>Try &quot;Manual Reconciliation&quot;.</p>
<ul>
<li>Step 1: Log into your account.</li>
<li>Step 2: Tap on your Account&#39;s Balance on the top-right corner.</li>
<li><p>Step 3: Select &quot;Transactions&quot; to view your transaction details.</p>
<p>  <img src="../../../../assets/wap-was-deposit-unsuccessful-1.png" alt=""></p>
</li>
<li><p>Step 4: Tap on &quot;Was your Deposit unsuccessful?&quot; right above the transaction list</p>
<p>  <img src="../../../../assets/wap-was-deposit-unsuccessful-2.png" alt=""></p>
</li>
<li><p>Step 5: Enter the M-Pesa Transaction Code which M-Pesa sent to your Mobile Phone via SMS. If under the listed situations (a. Deposit displayed as &quot;Failed&quot;; b. Deposit is displayed as &quot;Pending&quot;; c. M-pesa Paybill was used to Deposit, but no records exist), the Deposit transaction&#39;s Balance will most probably be added to your account after your confirmation. If this did not work, please contact Customer Care.</p>
<p>  <img src="../../../../assets/wap-was-deposit-unsuccessful-3.png" alt=""></p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>